node.text:
Which of these 9 destinations in Norway would you visit? 🇳🇴 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on nomadfervor.com (link in my bio: @nomadfervor)

Comment below 

1. Voss
2. Geiranger
3. Loen
4. Narvik
5. Vestlandet
6. Møre og Romsdal
7. Stryn
8. Sunnmørsalpene
9. Sogn og Fjordane

📽 @oyehaug
📍Norway

node.text:
Wild ride 🐎 You can check how to get your photos promoted in our account, use the link in our bio @nomadfervor

Bareback riding is a form of horseback riding without a saddle. It requires skill, balance, and coordination, as the rider does not have any equipment to compensate for errors of balance or skill.

Proponents of bareback riding argue that riding in this fashion is natural, allows considerable communication with the horse, and improves a rider's balance. The drawbacks include a higher risk of injury due to an increased risk of falling off the horse, the potential to develop poor riding form, and the possibility of considerable discomfort to both horse and rider due to the absence of a supporting tree and any padding between the rider's seat bones and the horse's spine. Over time, it is more fatiguing to both horse and rider to ride bareback.

📽 @kerrikasem
🎶 Sting - Desert Rose (feat. Cheb Mami)
📍 Essaouira, Morocco

node.text:
Adventure calling🌲🌅 We can post your photos in our account, follow the link in our bio: @nomadfervor and we will select your pictures

Would you visit Finland during the summer?

While Finland is usually associated with snow draped mountains and Christmas getaways, it’s definitely worth visiting during the warmer months as well! Escape to the countryside in a lakeside cottage, take on stunning hillside hikes, or stay up all night to enjoy Finland’s midnight sun. 🇫🇮

📷 @jukkarisikko

Have you ever seen @nature hummocks? 😍 You can check how to get your photos promoted in our account, use the link in our bio @nomadfervor

The wonderland of Puga Valley in Ladakh, India via @apytravelstories will left you speechless 🤯 If you are a @nature lover, then you should really visit this place. It's incredible landscape attracts the visitors.

The Puga valley in the Changthang valley lies at about 22 km to the east of the Salt Lake valley across the Polokonka La pass (5,350 m). It is famous for its borax and sulphur deposits and hot water springs.
